{"id": "EUVD-2025-15930", "enisaUuid": "85eeacc0-dbeb-34aa-84ef-c59addd49ca4", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nublk: fix race between io_uring_cmd_complete_in_task and ublk_cancel_cmd\n\nublk_cancel_cmd() calls io_uring_cmd_done() to complete uring_cmd, but\nwe may have scheduled task work via io_uring_cmd_complete_in_task() for\ndispatching request, then kernel crash can be triggered.\n\nFix it by not trying to canceling the command if ublk block request is\nstarted.", "datePublished": "2025-05-20T18:30:54", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-17T18:30:23", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-37906", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f40139fde5278d81af3227444fd6e76a76b9506d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/fb2eb9ddf556f93fef45201e1f9d2b8674bcc975"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-37906", "GHSA-mrmf-653p-5vh8"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "34338f74-f997-3b66-b14c-8342062c8535", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15"}, {"id": "531edfc5-4d2c-30ea-a50f-83461831c59f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "6922ec0c-43fb-324f-9c5e-17b42ae9d164", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.7"}, {"id": "8bcaaf09-6f3f-3065-a1f0-64d03b6f25d4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "216c8f5ef0f209a3797292c487bdaa6991ab4b92 <fb2eb9ddf556f93fef45201e1f9d2b8674bcc975"}, {"id": "aff33989-ae91-3770-bb7b-2b2b14570186", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.14.6"}, {"id": "da778cd1-6b38-3531-959a-906e3e3e46c0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "216c8f5ef0f209a3797292c487bdaa6991ab4b92 <f40139fde5278d81af3227444fd6e76a76b9506d"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "4272221e-cf08-358a-a0bb-639b39d5b1e7", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}